## Usage Patterns

### Showcase

```tsx
() => (
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '32px' }}>
    <div>
      <Link
        data-automation-id="basicLink"
        href="https://intuit.com"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        Intuit
      </Link>
    </div>
    <div>
      <Link
        data-automation-id="ariaLabelLink"
        href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Techniques/aria/ARIA8"
        aria-label="Learn more about aria-label"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        Learn more
      </Link>
      <div>
        <B3>
          Aria-label should be provided to give more context to screenreader
          users
        </B3>
        <B3>
          In the above example, aria-label is <b>Learn more about aria-label</b>
        </B3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <Link
        data-automation-id="withTargetLink"
        href="https://intuit.com"
        target="_blank"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        Link with target
      </Link>
    </div>
    <div>
      This link is{' '}
      <Link
        type="inline"
        data-automation-id="inlineLink"
        href="https://intuit.com"
        target="_blank"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        inline
      </Link>{' '}
      with other content.
    </div>
    <div>
      <Link
        data-automation-id="withTargetLink"
        href="https://intuit.com"
        target="_blank"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        Link with icon
        <CaretRight />
      </Link>
    </div>
    <div>
      <Link
        data-automation-id="withTargetLink"
        href="https://intuit.com"
        target="_blank"
        type="secondary"
        onClick={action('link clicked!')}
      >
        Secondary link with icon
        <CaretRight />
      </Link>
    </div>
  </div>
)
```

## Accessibility

### Keyboard Navigation

- **Tab** allows users to jump to the next link in a group of links or the next element on the screen.
- **Shift + Tab** allows users to jump to the previous link in a group of links or the previous element on the screen.
- **Enter** allows users to activate a link

